<h1>Scoresheet Instructions</h1>

<div class="section-title">Live Scoresheet</div>
<p>Use the digital scoresheet here:<br>
<a href="https://rownpoolleague.github.io/scores/" style="color:#4af;">https://rownpoolleague.github.io/scores/</a></p>

<div class="section-title">How to Use the Scoresheet</div>

<p><strong>1. Select Teams</strong><br>
Choose the Home Team and Away Team from the dropdown menus. Rosters load automatically.</p>

<p><strong>2. Assign Lag Winner / Lag Loser</strong><br>
Tap a player name from either roster. The system fills Lag Winner and Lag Loser automatically.</p>

<p><strong>3. Enter Total Match Innings</strong><br>
Use the + / – buttons to adjust the total innings.</p>

<p><strong>4. Enter Player Stats</strong><br>
Each player has the following stats:<br>
- HC = Handicap<br>
- Wins = Games won<br>
- Safeties = Defensive shots<br>
- 8B = Legal 8‑ball made<br>
- B+R = Break and run<br>
- E8 = Early 8‑ball</p>

<p><strong>5. Match Winner</strong><br>
This field auto‑fills based on total wins.</p>

<p><strong>6. Submit Match</strong><br>
Press “Submit Match”. The button disables and a message appears:<br>
“Please wait while your results are submitted…”<br>
When complete:<br>
“Match submitted successfully. You may now enter the next match.”</p>

<div class="section-title">How Submissions Work</div>
<p>
1. The scoresheet sends the match data to a Google Apps Script endpoint.<br>
2. The script writes the results into the league’s master Google Sheet.<br>
3. The button re‑enables once the server confirms the write.
</p>

<div class="section-title">Updating Rosters</div>
<p>
Rosters are stored in <strong>script.js</strong>.<br>
To update:<br>
1. Open script.js<br>
2. Find the roster object<br>
3. Add or remove players<br>
4. Save and commit<br>
Changes go live immediately.
</p>

<a class="back-button" href="index.html">Back to Main Menu</a>

